Title: Local News Digest — New York City, NY
Date: December 31, 2025

1) **Zohran Mamdani to Be Sworn in as NYC Mayor** — Democratic state assemblyman Zohran Mamdani is set to become New York City's next mayor as the clock strikes midnight on New Year's Day. He has chosen the historic, now-abandoned Old City Hall subway station for a private ceremony, with New York State Attorney General Letitia James administering the oath. A public ceremony will follow on the steps of City Hall, officiated by Senator Bernie Sanders, featuring a block party on Broadway with music, performances, and interfaith elements. ([time.com](https://time.com/7342810/mamdani-swearing-in-ceremony-nyc-mayor/?utm_source=openai))

2) **New York City Weather Forecast** — As of 3:39 PM on December 31, 2025, the current conditions in New York City are partly sunny with a temperature of 28°F (-2°C). The forecast for Wednesday, December 31, 2025, is breezy with clouds and breaks of sun, with a high of 37°F (3°C) and a low of 32°F (0°C). Thursday, January 1, 2026, is expected to have a couple of flurries in the morning, otherwise breezy with times of clouds and sun, with a high of 33°F (1°C) and a low of 22°F (-6°C). For the complete forecast, please refer to the detailed weather information provided earlier.

